Fox News anchor Chris Wallace Christopher (Chris) WallacePelosi to appear on 'Fox News Sunday' for first time since 2017 Trump lashes out at New York Times over report on coronavirus response Fox News host hits back at Trump over Chris Wallace criticism: 'Enough' MORE will interview Speaker Nancy Pelosi Nancy PelosiLady Gaga calls WHO chief a 'superstar' McCarthy says he supports incorporating hospital funding into small business aid package Trump criticizes Pelosi over stalemate on small business loan funds MORE (D-Calif.) on Sunday, marking her first interview on the network since 2017, according to a release from Fox.
Pelosi will join "Fox News Sunday" to "discuss the current state of the U.S. amid the coronavirus pandemic, negotiations to revive the small business loan program and much more," per the network.
"I heard one of them say: 'Well, people will die — or we'll open up the economy and people will die — so that's the lesser of two evils,'" Pelosi said, referring to remarks from a GOP congressman.
Pelosi's last appearance on Fox News in July 2017 was also with Wallace.
She was the House minority leader at the time.